annotationA: Probable glutamine-dependent NAD(+) synthetase; ATP binding; NAD+ synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing) activity; hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds. It is involved in the biological process described with: NAD biosynthetic process; In the C-terminal section; belongs to the NAD synthetase family
annotationB: NAD kinase 2, mitochondrial; Mitochondrial NAD(+) kinase that phosphorylates NAD(+) to yield NADP(+). Can use both ATP or inorganic polyphosphate as the phosphoryl donor
